cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with network management protocols and network monitoring, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic admission approaches, which are relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a hardware-friendly variant of the algorithm, which could be of interest to the systems and control (cs.SI) sub-category.
